Lonicera sempervirens is a species of twining, woody vine. 
It is also known as trumpet honeysuckle due to its tube-shaped, brightly colored flowers. 
The flowers are typically a deep red-orange color, but they can also be pink or yellow. 
The leaves of this plant are green and evergreen, and have a glossy, smooth texture. 
Lonicera sempervirens is often found in woodland and along stream banks. 
It is native to the eastern United States and is commonly used as an ornamental plant. 
This species of honeysuckle is also known for attracting hummingbirds and butterflies with its nectar-rich flowers.
